@spec mm_collision_backstop_spec  src=tests/specs/mm_collision_backstop_spec.lua  loc=107  sha=70ef819  cases=4
@exercises midiManager (h.mm)
@surface   mm:notes, mm:subscribe, mm:byUuid, mm:modify, mm:assign
@harness   bareMM

# Intent
  Phase 2 pin - design/same-pitch-enforcement.md item 2. mm's write-path
  backstop: a verb filing over a live collisionIdx slot records (chan, pitch);
  the outermost modify unwind resolves the settled model via
  voicing.resolveGroup and fires collisionsResolved. bareMM on purpose:
  with tm wired, its reload rebuild separates the collision first and the
  backstop (correctly) finds nothing.

# Helpers
  @fn ppqsOf(mm)  @ 10-15
  @fn noteAt(mm, ppq)  @ 17-19
  @fn twoVoices(harness)  @ 22-27
      -- Two distinct voices (different ppqL) on one (chan, pitch).

# Cases
  @case 'distinct voices colliding via direct mm:assign are nudged apart'  [harness]  @ 31-50
  @case 'true duplicates (same ppqL, same detune) collapse to the longer'  [harness]  @ 54-73
  @case 'resolution is idempotent - the next modify finds nothing'  [harness]  @ 77-88
  @case 'a transient mid-batch collision resolves to nothing'  [harness]  @ 92-105

# Uses (outbound edges)
  @use call mm:notes  @ 12,18
  @use call mm:subscribe  @ 36,62,81,96
  @use call mm:byUuid  @ 38,70
  @use call mm:modify  @ 41,64,83,84,98
  @use call mm:assign  @ 41,64,83,84,99,100
